    • Method Detail

      • saveToString

        String saveToString()
        Returns this configuration's YAML representation as text.

        Returns the representation as text of the data in this configuration, appointed for being saved inside a file and without indication on whether it should be formatted or minimized.

        Usually, will be the formatted version to allow humans to read the contents of the file easily, but might be a minimized version or even one between both.

        Specified by:
        saveToString in interface IHRConfiguration
        Returns:
        this configuration's YAML representation

      • loadFromString

        void loadFromString(String data)
        Loads the provided YAML data into this YAMLConfig.

        Reads the required data from the specified string. The string can be the result of saveToString, toFormattedString or toMinimizedString, or can come from any other source provided that its format is correct and readable by a computer.

        Specified by:
        loadFromString in interface IHRConfiguration
        Parameters:
        data - The YAML data as text
